programme.title: Ika-6 Na Utos
إكا-6 نا أوتوس
programme.desc: The story of a married couple where the husband is having an extra marital affair and will leave his loyal, caring and chubby wife for his seductive mistress. جي أم إيه بينوي تي هي قناة ترفيه على مدار الساعة طوال الأسبوع حيث تتضمن مسلسلات حديثة، كوميدية، حوارية، واقعية، مسلية ومتنوعة فضلاً عن برامج إخبارية من قناة جي أم إيه في الفيليبين. باللغتين الإنكليزية والفيليبينية

The last time we saw crime-solving crack team Brennan and Booth, the forensic anthropologist stunned her FBI partner with news that she was pregnant with his child. Entering season seven, we pick up with the pair, well into Brennan's pregnancy, as they adjust to their new life as an expectant couple and deal with the forthcoming changes. Still seeing the world from radically different perspectives, Brennan and Booth will also continue to deal with a series of gruesome and baffling crimes

programme.title: Bones

programme.title: Bones

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The Method in the Madness. Booth invites Sweets to stay at the family home, but soon regrets it. The team investigate what they suspect to be a modern-day Jack the Ripper

programme.title: Hawaii Five-0
programme.desc: Ohana. When a former cyber terrorism expert is kidnapped, McGarrett & his team are assigned to find the missing expert in order to protect national security

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Bottomless. In a case inspired by a true-life incident, a shady businessman becomes the chief suspect in the murder of a young lawyer

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Driven. The daddy of the crime drama genre displays its pedigree with a racially-charged and engaging episode. Green (Jesse L Martin) and Lupo (Jeremy Sisto) are thrown into the thick of the action when a white teenager and a young black girl are shot dead. The investigation threatens to collapse before it's even begun when the locals remain tight-lipped about events that may have triggered the tragedy, but the detectives refuse to back down. Their dogged determination pays off when they discover that one of the victims had been involved in an altercation with a neighbour. Will this lead prove fruitful?

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Political Animal. Blood continues to spill on the mean streets of New York. Green (Jesse L Martin) and Lupo (Jeremy Sisto) are tested by a triple homicide, which they initially decide is the grisly result of a lovers' quarrel. As ever, appearances are deceiving and nothing is as it first seems. On closer inspection, the detectives uncover a link to a conman with political connections

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Scry Hard. Zankou (Oded Fehr) goes to incredibly complex lengths to lure the Charmed Ones into his demonic lair. Meanwhile, one of Zankou's minions turns the girls' mansion inside out in hopes of locating the spiritual nexus that will release the Shadow, thereby imbuing Zankou with the "Ultimate Power." In order to protect his parents, Piper (Holly Marie Combs) and Leo (Brian Krause), from the impending demon assault, baby Wyatt shrinks them both and locks them in a tiny dollhouse -- with neither parent aware of the other's plight!

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Little Box of Horrors. The sisters hunt for Pandora's Box which has fallen into the hands of a demon who intends to spread its sorrows all over the world

programme.title: Charmed

programme.desc: Of Grave Importance. Sam and Dean reconnect with an old hunter friend who suddenly disappears in an abandoned house that is haunted by a powerful ghost

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Reading Is Fundamental. Sam and Dean provoke Dick Roman's stormy temper when they steal his clay tablet. Castiel regains his memory, but is he well enough to help the boys?

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The Patriot in Purgatory. Brennan experiments with basketball to help turn the squinterns into a team, while Booth investigates remains linked to the 9/11 terrorist attacks

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The Bod in the Pod. The team hit the beach to examine a strange pod containing gelatinised remains. Hodgins is convinced it's of alien origin, but Brennan detects foul play

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The But in the Joke. A street artist who is plastering his work on a billboard falls into his glue—and onto a corpse—so the team try to get him unstuck from the remains as they also work to identify the body. Meanwhile, Booth takes a stab at stand-up comedy at a club's open-mike night to look for suspects; and Angela finds herself attracted to the street artist

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The Ghost in the Machine. A psychic joins the investigation of the death of a little boy whose soul is believed to be still alive, prompting the team members to reflect on their beliefs of life after death

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The Diamond in the Rough. When a professional ballroom dancer is killed before her audition for a reality-TV dance competition, Brennan and Booth pose as potential contestants to hunt for suspects

programme.title: Bones

programme.title: Get Hard

programme.title: Why Did I Get Married?
programme.desc: Tyler Perry wrote, produced, directed and stars in this touching and insightful comedy-drama that he adapted from his successful stage play. Four close couples hash out a variety of relationship issues while on vacation in the Colorado mountains, where a marital blizzard blows in when one of them arrives sans wife but with mistress in tow

programme.title: Think Like a Man
programme.desc: This adaptation of Steve Harvey's non-fiction relationship advice book Act Like a Lady, Think Like a Man focuses on six friends who regularly get together to play basketball, and usually are commiserating about women issues. Jeremy (Jerry Ferrara) is a geeky pothead and comic-book obsessive whose career is stuck in neutral and who won't pop the question to his girlfriend of nine years. Zeke (Romany Malco) is a former musician-turned-businessman who is great at picking up the ladies but can't commit to a long-term relationship. Michael (Terrence J) is good looking and charming, but his mother still has him wrapped around her finger and doesn't want to let him go. Dominic (Michael Ealy) keeps changing career goals, and while he's an excellent chef, he hasn't found a way to make it pay. And short, motormouthed Cedric (Kevin Hart) is in the midst of a divorce and can't wait to be free of his wife. Nerdy but well-meaning Bennett (Gary Owen) is the only one in a functioning relationship, and he gets a lot of grief from his buddies for his happy marriage(n)

programme.title: Arrow
programme.desc: The Recruits. Oliver's new recruits for Team Arrow are Curtis, Wild Dog and Evelyn Sharp. Unfortunately, the Green Arrow's training methods prove to be too much for some of them to handle. In flashbacks, Oliver's initiation into the Bratva continues(n)

programme.title: Arrow
programme.desc: A Matter of Trust. Green Arrow is forced to battle new drug dealer Garret Runnels, who is terrorizing Star City, after Wild Dog strikes out on his own to take the dealer down but quickly learns he's not up to the task(n)

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Quit Claim. Mad Men's January Jones takes temporary leave of the 1960s for a stint on television's most durable cop show. The offensively beautiful blonde proves indispensable in Green and Lupo's latest investigation, a complicated hit-and-run. All the evidence leads to a real estate scam artist, but the detectives have to overcome a niggling obstacle: he's pulled a vanishing act. With the help of Jones's insurance agency employee, Green and Lupo launch an undercover operation to lure the suspect out of hiding. When the sting goes wrong, the case is turned on its head - is the conman the culprit after all?(n)

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Death Becomes Them. Zankou's latest victim is Phoebe's fellow grad student Tim (Colin Egglesfield), who drops dead at her feet. Convinced that Tim's demise is entirely her fault (she has in fact been "accused" by the dead man's spirit), Phoebe (Alyssa Milano) asks Daryl (Dorian Gregory) to investigate the phenomenon -- while Zankou mounts his next and even more horrible offense. Meanwhile, Paige (Rose McGowan) senses that her new student Joanna (Laura Regan) has the "wrongest" boyfriend of all time, and Piper (Holly Marie Combs) and Leo (Brian Krause) forget their past differences to plan a birthday party for baby Chris(n)

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Something Wicca This Way Goes...?. The sisters are forced to make a terrifying choice between sacrificing their powers or their lives, just as the legal investigation into their affairs gathers new momentum(n)

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: There Will Be Blood. Sam and Dean must locate three key items to defeat Dick Roman and the Leviathans, and Castiel aids them in their request. Meanwhile, Bobby attempts a new ghost trick that turns out to be extremely dangerous(n)

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Survival of the Fittest. The final episode of the sensationally spooky seventh season brings the long-awaited clash between the Winchester brothers and the Leviathans(n)

programme.sub-title: We Need to Talk About Kevin
